{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-learning-center-learning-center-template-tsx","path":"/learn/cash-management/what-is-sipc-protection/","result":{"pageContext":{"contentfulData":{"metaTitle":" What Does SIPC Protection Cover? | Brex","metaDescription":"The SIPC runs a protection scheme to cover deposits on certain investments and securities. Find out all about it with Brex.","heroReference":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"2JOT7lk0e2rN9IdeSEbfBk","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:08.970Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-14T21:43:58.915Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":9,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"articleCover"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"image":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"2bW6B8WoNNhBHizXAxOvSp","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-09-18T09:54:20.799Z","updatedAt":"2019-09-18T09:54:20.799Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"title":"cardSmall","file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/lrdkz6qgi9tt/2bW6B8WoNNhBHizXAxOvSp/c7c04c1e59eddc1d2dfbb71ccf4c6c42/cardSmall.png","details":{"size":243289,"image":{"width":831,"height":825}},"fileName":"cardSmall.png","contentType":"image/png"}}},"title":"What is SIPC protection?","imgAlt":"sipc","subtitle":"SIPC protection offers protection on certain investments and securities.","ctaSubtitle":"Find out exactly what SIPC protection covers, what the limit is and why it is set at that level."}},"contentReference":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"65sPrYIyAssZk8fzGoEUuA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:23.020Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:23.020Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"SIPC protection is a deposit protection scheme on investments and securities. The non-profit Securities Investor Protection Corporation (SIPC) runs the scheme. Broker/Dealer members pay a percentage of their gross revenues as their premium.\n\nThis membership corporation protects the customers of broker-dealers. The coverage is in the event that the broker/dealer fails, and has co-mingled the funds of customer accounts with the broker/dealer’s operating account. \nThe broker-dealer first uses its remaining capital and securities to cover customers' deposits. SIPC protection covers the rest if there is not enough money for all customers' securities.\n"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"71BmuwzRBGXwvY8Z6LrIfP","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:35.525Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:35.525Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionTitle"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"What does SIPC protection cover?"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"1CM1iSZSa5RNxkUyJdjPJY","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:50.464Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:42:50.464Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"SIPC protection covers investments including $250,000 in cash. SIPC covers brokerage accounts up to $500,000 in securities, of which $250,000 can be cash."}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"6W320CsexsQLrkiVtVS8d1","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:43:04.690Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:43:04.690Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionTitle"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":" Is there a limit to SIPC protection?"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"4xcYWH3sE3WoIr2eHGg4Yf","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:44:05.696Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:44:05.696Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"Like most financial policies, SIPC protection has a limit. But it is not as simple as putting a single total on all your investments. It depends on if you hold any of your investments as cash.\n\nThe SIPC protection limit has two parts:\n1. Up to $250,000 cash held.\n2. Up to $500,000 total securities.\n\n### Example One:\nYou have total securities worth $400,000. Of this, $200,000 is in cash and $200,000 is in other securities.\n\nYou are under the $250,000 limit for cash and the $500,000 total limit. The SIPC protection scheme would cover the total amount.\n\n### Example Two:\nYou have total securities worth $400,000. Of this, $300,000 is in cash and $100,000 is in other securities.\n\nSIPC protection would cover the first $250,000 of your cash and the $100,000 in non-cash securities.\n\nYour total protection would be $350,000. You would lose your cash over the $250,000 limit.\n\nIf you deposit large sums of money, remember the $250,000 cash limit. This can affect your total payout on investments from $250,000 to $500,000. \n"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"75pEeXD0ne85X8NhPIObk0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:44:16.768Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:44:16.768Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionTitle"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"Why is the SIPC protection limit set at $500,000?"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"7AORYIVSC2dbTiBpaGFgNR","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:44:32.159Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:44:32.159Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"The SIPC has existed for half a century. There have been very few cases where a broker went out of business and investors lost money because of it. This is because customer accounts are segregated and are not co-mingled with Brex. Brex cannot use customer funds or securities as part of their day-to-day operations. If the broker/dealer fails, the customer’s account is transferred in whole to another broker/dealer.\n\nSIPC protection makes sure investors get their money back in these very rare events. It protects the custody of those funds against the broker-dealer's failure.\n"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"2KkcAjabkdUFi57EO0yF14","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-25T20:48:47.643Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-25T20:48:47.643Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"fourStepTile"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"articleLinks":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"6wtO169VuBX2rZ7pqfwMYb","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-11-14T17:16:05.086Z","updatedAt":"2019-11-14T17:16:05.086Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"articleHeader"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"category":"cash-management","thumbnailImage":{"sys":{"space